{"word":"ὄροφος","slug":"ὄροφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὄροφος</b></el> <el>(ὄροφος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐρέφω'><el>ἐρέφω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>in collective sense, <i>the reeds used for thatching houses</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:ὀροφή'><el>ὀροφή</el></a>, <i>a roof</i>, Orac. <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}